USEFUL COMMANDS IN PAPARAZZI :

- Command to run the optitrack for external pose, you can use the following command (EKF2) from the paparazzi directory: 
$ ./sw/ground_segment/python/natnet3.x/natnet2ivy.py --long_edge right --x_side right --ac_nose right -ac "rigid_body_id" "drone_id" -o
(where "drone_id" is the UAV id and "rigid_body_id" is the optitrack recorded rigid body id)

- Command to run on the ship box's Raspberry pi to forward the telemetry message from the ship box AP to the common wireless network: 
$ ./paparazzi/sw/misc/link/pprzlink_router_cc -e uart:///dev/ttyS0:460800 -e udp://0.0.0.0:4343:192.168.1.ip_laptop:4342
(where ttyS0 is the Raspberry pi UART port where the AutoPilot is connected and 4342/4343 is the udp ports where the telemetry packets is forwarded)

- Command to forward the RTCM message from the ship box GPS to the common wireless network: 
$ ./paparazzi/sw/misc/link/pprzlink_router_cc -e uart:///dev/ttyS4:460800 -e udp://0.0.0.0:4253:192.168.1.255:4252 &
(where ttyS1 is the Raspberry pi UART port where the GPS is connected, 460800 is the baudrate of the UART communication and 4252/4253 is the udp port where the telemetry packets are forwarded)

- Command to forward the SHIP_INFO_MSG message from a local udp port on the drone's IVY bus: 
$ ./paparazzi/sw/ground_segment/ship_box/Pixhawk_4_read_msg_v2 -i "drone_id" -s "ship box id (should be 5)"

- Command to forward the GPS RTCM messages from a local udp port on the shared wireless network to the drone's IVY bus: 
$ ./paparazzi/sw/ground_segment/misc/ublox2ivy -i "drone_id" -e udp://0.0.0.0:4252:192.168.1.255:4253 &
(where 4252/4253 is the udp port where the RTCM packets are received on the common wireless network)

- Command to forward the GPS RTCM messages from a local UART port to the drone: 
$ ./paparazzi/sw/ground_segment/misc/ublox2ivy -i "drone_id" -e uart:///dev/ttyS1:460800
(where ttyS1 is the UART port where the RTCM packets are received and 460800 is the baudrate of the UART communication)

- Connect wirelessly to the Herelink using adb: 
$ adb connect 192.168.1.101:5555 
(where 192.168.1.101 is the herelink Ip address in the shared wireless network)

- Command for the Herelink to forward udp telemetry packets from the UAV to the common wireless network: 
$ adb shell /oem/bin/pprzlink_router_cc -e udp://192.168.0.11:5242:192.168.0.10:5243 -e udp://0.0.0.0:4243:192.168.1.ip_laptop:4242 & 

- Command for Herelink to forward udp telemetry packets from the UAV to the USB local thetering:  
$ adb shell /oem/bin/pprzlink_router_cc -e udp://192.168.0.11:5242:192.168.0.10:5243 -e udp://0.0.0.0:4243:192.168.42.255:4242 & 

- Install dependencies needed for the Aruco detection algorithm in sw/ext/aruco_detection: 
$ pip3 install opencv-python opencv-contrib-python pymap3d pyserial
$ pip3 install numpy --upgrade

- Save PAPARAZZI_HOME env variable in linux: 
$ sudo nano /etc/environment --> add a line --> PAPARAZZI_HOME="/home/USER/paparazzi"

- Local IP Address for the Opi external network card for the SIXDOF system: 
$ sudo nano /etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml
    network:
    version: 2
    renderer: networkd
    ethernets:
        network card name:
        dhcp4: no
        addresses:
            - 192.168.10.100/24
        nameservers:
            addresses:
            - 8.8.8.8
            - 8.8.4.4
$ sudo netplan apply